<br>
<br>
I have no problem with requiring people to be present in order to assist.  I think it's fair to make them be vulnerable.  I also wonder how you would need buffs to scout past the mg from pk.  That's a good distance.  Sure you might die, but if that distance is there then the odds are that the other guy doesn't have buffs.  So then it's an even fight.  If his buffer is close enough thus is life.  If he's in a team you were dead anyway.<br>
<br>
I hope these sort of changes go in.  Otherwise, I will have to get a buff bot myself just to keep up.<br>
<br>
Mel. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/umelanu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>melanu</A> at: 7/7/02 11:05:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/ubrandynaquilius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brandyn Aquilius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/8/02 1:33:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3701.topic&index=20>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> See, that's the thing.  Buff bots aren't EVIL.  They're just a little shady IMO.  So, since as of now they are perfectly legal, I'll just get one and hope that they put in a  range restriction.  If they don't, then I'll just bot.  Simple. <p>-Aurra Sing-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/umelanu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>melanu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/8/02 3:33:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3701.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Was thinking about this...<br>
<br>
What if they put in the range restriction and then added that the buffing classes get a higher % of the groups rps..based on the fact that they can't do damage and get their own very easily. <br>
<br>
If these went together it would hurt buff bots, but help buffers.  <br>
<br>
I want to add that it doesn't just affect my playstyle but it impacts the game.  I see lots of buff bots sitting in the emain pk.  How is it fair to have that ability that no one can impact.<br>
<br>
Heh the one I thought was interesting is a healer I know had a skald bot.  The skald was there just to run the healer around at high speeds while he mesed.  Fear that healer.<br>
<br>
Mel   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/ulandril77.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Landril77</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/8/02 5:36:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3701.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> I try to do my part to discourage buff bots.  A while ago I sat around the PK for a few hours and tried to figure out which clerics belonged to which infs.  Now I keep a list handy so that whenever I see those clerics parked in the pk I remind my guild to spam the inf with messages requesting buffs or a rez fromt he buff-bot.<br>
<br>
I rarely have more than base-line friar buffs on, and commonly not even those because when I'm in groups I usually suggest the buffs go to the healers or casters to keep them alive longer.  Sure the buffs help out my damage output, but my main effectiveness comes from scouting and disrupting key targets than fromt he actual damage I do when I'm in a good group, so keeping the other key people healthy is usually the better way to go.  I'm a suicide bomber in most fights.  Take out a key target or two then make my getaway or more often enjoy my view from the floor of the battlefield until my rez arrives. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/ushaftoe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shaftoe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/8/02 7:27:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3701.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> *I remind my guild to spam the inf with messages requesting buffs or a rez fromt he buff-bot*<br>
<br>
So what's the name/server of this guild of annoying spammers?<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/umithar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mithar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/8/02 8:18:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3701.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .bots</span><hr size=1> a large range on buffs would be a nice answer.<br>
large enough that if your grp`d you wont loose your buffs or you could make them work like a chant/shout that when you go out of range while grps they go away, but come back when you hit range again. this would solve the recast delema <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/ubaym.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Baym</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/8/02 9:27:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3701.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .bots</span><hr size=1> No offense, but the fact that clerics can buff beyond the AF armor cap just imbalances infiltrators more over other assassins. SBs and NS's are capped at 550 AF unless they have a charged item or a Realm Ability. Combine all the recent changes to the game, buffed SBs will hit buffed infiltrators for significantly less than before. Thrust infiltrators with Vanish essentially are the only assassins that could replicate the prowess of the Crit Blade in deep penetration killing. Thrust infiltrators will have huge AF and hit points (via cleric buffs which are far better than healer or shaman buffs). They will be able to attack chain classes well behind enemy lines and with their high poison skill (more spec pts higher than SBs) disable or kill a person before any help can be mustered. I have seen Animalia on Galahad kill 2 level 48+ chain classes, a healer and a thane, without restealthing. If the numbers go against the infiltrator, Vanish and move away.<br>
<br>
The sad thing is those screenshots with huge doublefrost damage that contributed to doublefrost being nerfed were by people with buff bots. I do not like nerfs, but hopefully Mythic will do something about them. They severely unbalance the game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/ushadowerbdc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ShadowerBDC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/8/02 11:28:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3701.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .bots</span><hr size=1> Baym,<br>
<br>
